<Base
  title="Terms of service — Elevatek"
  description="The terms that govern Elevatek's website and consulting engagements."
  noindex={true}
  minimalFooter={true}
>
  <section class="page-hero"><div class="wrap">
    <p class="eyebrow">Legal</p>
    <h1>Terms of service</h1>
  </div></section>
  <div class="wrap"><div class="page">
    <p class="updated">Draft — last updated June 2026</p>
    <div class="flag">Draft for review. Confirm with counsel before launch; engagement specifics live in each statement of work.</div>

    <h2>The basics</h2>
    <p>This site is operated by Elevatek Consulting Inc. ("Elevatek", "we"). Using the site means you accept these terms. Consulting engagements are governed first by their signed statement of work or written agreement; these terms fill the gaps.</p>

    <h2>Services</h2>
    <p>We provide consulting on GTM systems: implementation, integration, fractional revenue operations, and related coaching. Scope, timeline, and fees for any engagement are set in writing before work starts.</p>

    <h2>Intellectual property</h2>
    <p>On full payment, you own the deliverables we build for you in an engagement. We keep ownership of our pre-existing tools, templates, and methods, and you get a license to keep using anything of ours embedded in your deliverables.</p>

    <h2>Confidentiality</h2>
    <p>We treat your data and business information as confidential, and we expect the same for ours. A signed agreement can extend this further.</p>

    <h2>Liability</h2>
    <p>To the extent the law allows, our total liability for any engagement is capped at the fees you paid us for that engagement, and neither side is liable for indirect or consequential damages.</p>

    <h2>Governing law</h2>
    <p>These terms are governed by the laws of Québec and the federal laws of Canada that apply there.</p>

    <h2>Changes</h2>
    <p>If these terms change, the date above changes with it.</p>
  </div></div>
</Base>
